Proof of Proposition 2. Consider any P ∈ P(K) and assume ex absurdo that P ∈/ P. It then follows from Proposition 4 that there is some u ∈ L such that P(u) = P(u), or equivalently, such that P(u) + P(−u) = 0. Since we know from LP4 and LP3 that

